Mizuho Securities USA Inc. (MSUSA) is the U.S. securities and futures arm of the Japanese Financial services conglomerate Mizuho Financial Group. It specializes in underwriting, as well as the sales and trading of securities and exchange listed derivatives.
IT Structure
•The IT department stations personnel across the county and works in conjunction with IT executives from its parent company that operates from Japan.
•The IT department can be divided into two teams including infrastructure and applications.
•The application team oversees the… MoreIT Structure
•The IT department stations personnel across the county and works in conjunction with IT executives from its parent company that operates from Japan.
•The IT department can be divided into two teams including infrastructure and applications.
•The application team oversees the development, support, and implementation of the company's corporate and business systems and applications.
•The infrastructure team oversees the company's infrastructure which supports its business systems, applications, and the company's day-to-day activity.

IT Intelligence Snippets
2013
•The company's data center operates using Cisco UCS Blade Servers, Data Domain and NetApp storage technologies.
•The company recently completed an initiative to migrate its financial systems to Bloomberg's trading platform.
•Currently exploring Cloud technology implementing ServiceNow and Oracle Identity Management.

2012
•As of Q3, looking to deploy non-Blackberry mobile device solutions over the next 12 months.





